Xzavion Curry (CLE) has a fastball with a ton of riding action and a pair of nasty breaking balls. A super athletic pitcher, Curry repeats his mechanics well and pounds the zone.

Take a look at this curve. https://t.co/TsOvKKvvZ1

Graham Ashcraft (CIN) is disgusting on the bump. The guy throws gyro cutters in the upper 90s that are reminiscent of Emmanuel Clase.

He was 1 of 3 pitchers in MiLB with a K% above 25% and GB% above 55%. https://t.co/MX66rLVbBG

Curtis Mead (TB) is not underrated on @JustBBMedia's Top 100 list, ranked No. 58 overall, however he does not get enough love in the industry.

Another plus hit tool guy with a fantastic feel for the strike zone and defense versatility, Mead is reminiscent of DJ LeMahieu https://t.co/asPheRUv7q
I mean...look at this throw from Rodriguez. This is just ridiculous stuff. Rodriguez has a plus hit tool and burgeoning power. Needs to be on everyone's radar. https://t.co/KCNsbqeIMJ

Endy Rodriguez (PIT) is a guy who I admittedly overlooked in the 2021 Pirates top prospect write ups. He is incredibly polished at the plate. 

A switch hitting catcher who stays on his back hip exceptionally well from both sides and has a rocket arm behind the dish. https://t.co/bChoZNnnQz

As you can see in the video below, Jhonkensy Noel (CLE) is an absolute menace.

8 of his 19 home runs were hit 110+ mph, including this one which was launched on a line at 115 mph. 19 years old in this video, Noel controls his body exceptionally well. https://t.co/e7ZhqIaLZn
